      <hedline>
        <hl1>Other Dual Winners</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marcella L Tobias letter on Jere Longman's July 25 article notes France's Marie-Jose Perec won 200 meters and 400 meters races in 1996 Olympics and American Valerie Briscoe-Hooks did same in 1984</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Focus Sharpens on Jones and Quest for Five Golds'' (July 25), Jere Longman states that no one but Michael Johnson has won the 200 meters and the 400 meters at the same Olympics. Au contraire.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''Focus Sharpens on Jones and Quest for Five Golds'' (July 25), Jere Longman states that no one but Michael Johnson has won the 200 meters and the 400 meters at the same Olympics. Au contraire.</p>
        <p>A woman, Marie-Jose Perec of France, won the 200 and 400 in the 1996 Olympics. And another woman, the American Valerie Briscoe-Hooks, won both races in the 1984 Olympics.</p>
        <p>MARCELLA L. TOBIAS  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
